    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-12-30T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-12-30T06:00:00-05:00" n="119"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d119">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/105</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Denmark</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_EMF1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Egan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Copenhagen</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-12-30T12:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 30, 1915, noon</hi>.</date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 5 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>204. <persName corresp="#p_FH1">Ford</persName> party disintegrated, ending in
                    [dissension?]. Mrs. <persName corresp="#p_SMR1">Schwimmer</persName>, the
                    leading spirit, has no plan.... No effect upon public opinion here: fiasco.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Minister</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
